x4freetext: The 1 MV Van de Graaff accelerator.
Surface barrier detectors with a sensitive
area  of 100 mm2 were used. The intrinsic  resolution
of detectors was measured to be 30 keV.
The carbon films were picked up on 2 cm*2 cm frames
which provided a 1.3 cm diameter circle available for
bombardment. The targets were usually 15 to 20
mu-g/cm2  thick and as such were about 6 keV thick to
Accuracy of the differential cross section data is
REACTION code in Sub 004-014 was changed.
Rutherford ratio is given in arbitrary units.
The targets were prepared by cracking methyl iodide
with a 13C enrichment of 65% onto a thin nickel backing
